# 2025 Responsive Design Patterns & Code Snippets

## CSS Flexbox Pattern
**Best for:** One-dimensional layouts (rows or columns)

```css
.nav {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
}
```

**Key strengths:** Intuitive for navigation bars, form elements, and card layouts with powerful spacing control via `gap`, `justify-content`, and `align-items`.

---

## CSS Grid Pattern
**Best for:** Two-dimensional layouts with rows and columns

```css
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
  gap: 1rem;
}
```

**Key strengths:** Precise structural control, supports named lines and grid areas, cleaner markup than nested Flexbox implementations.

---

## Container Queries Pattern
**Best for:** Modular, component-based responsive design

```css
.card {
  container-type: inline-size;
}

@container (min-width: 500px) {
  .card {
    flex-direction: row;
  }
}
```

**Key strengths:** Styles adapt based on container size rather than viewport; solves component reusability challenges in design systems.

---

## Use Case Decision Matrix

| Task | Flexbox | Grid | Container Queries |
|------|---------|------|-------------------|
| Navigation bars | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Photo galleries | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Design systems | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |

**Recommended approach:** Grid for page layout, Flexbox within sections, Container Queries for self-responsive cards.

